_channels.3.2</td></tr>\\n<tr><td>4</td><td>320</td><td>10240</td><td>(10240, 2048)</td><td>project_to_decoder_channels.4.2</td></tr></tbody></table>\\n    <p class=\\\"warn\\\">Audit finding: the model class default is <code>num_heads=1</code>, but the v1.1 predictor and checkpoint metadata use <code>num_heads=32</code>. P4/P6 should key off the actual checkpoint being loaded.</p>\\n  </section>\\n\\n  <section>\\n    <h2>Weight-Key Audit Input</h2>\\n    <p>Current Body-Tell can only directly reuse same-name/same-shape subsets before SP-A architecture work. This table is a baseline input for P6, not a claim that current Body-Tell is already checkpoint-compatible.</p>\\n    <table><thead><tr><th>Prefix</th><th>Body keys</th><th>Checkpoint keys</th><th>Same-name shape-compatible</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><code>decoder</code></td><td>32</td><td>508</td><td>0</td></tr>\\n<tr><td><code>encoder</code></td><td>30</td><td>448</td><td>0</td></tr>\\n<tr><td><code>mask_projections</code></td><td>16</td><td>0</td><td>0</td></tr>\\n<tr><td><code>pos_embed</code></td><td>0</td><td>1</td><td>0</td></tr>\\n<tr><td><code>project_bottleneck_embed</code></td><td>0</td><td>4</td><td>0</td></tr>\\n<tr><td><code>project_text_embed</code></td><td>4</td><td>4</td><td>4</td></tr>\\n<tr><td><code>project_to_decoder_channels</code></td><td>0</td><td>20</td><td>0</td></tr>\\n<tr><td><code>project_visual_embed</code></td><td>4</td><td>0</td><td>0</td></tr>\\n<tr><td><code>transformer_decoder</code></td><td>110</td><td>110</td><td>110</td></tr></tbody></table>\\n    <p>Same-name compatible current Body-Tell keys: <code>114</code>; shape mismatches: <code>0</code>; checkpoint keys unexpected to current Body-Tell: <code>981</code>.</p>\\n  </section>\\n\\n  <section>\\n    <h2>P6 Whitelist Input</h2>\\n    <h3>Required exact skips</h3>\\n    <table><thead><tr><th>Pattern</th><th>Reason</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><code>pos_embed</code></td><td>Body-Tell current non-192^3 crop uses dyna